A rule-based chatbot is an automated messaging system that follows predefined “if–then” rules to interact with users without using AI. A lead generation bot is designed to capture and qualify potential customers by asking structured questions and collecting contact details, making it useful for sales funnels and marketing campaigns. On platforms like Instagram, rule-based chatbots are commonly used in direct messages to respond instantly to keywords, deliver product information, and guide users toward sign-ups or purchases. In communities such as Discord, these bots automate moderation tasks, welcome new members, assign roles, and provide quick responses to commands, helping servers stay organized and engaging. Overall, rule-based chatbots are a reliable, low-complexity automation solution for improving customer interaction, lead conversion, and community management.
